<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>JENNEIRA'S HERE!</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20070726.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<br>
<b>Thursday, July 26, 2007</b> &mdash; Millsberry&#039;s citizens received a huge shock today as Jenneira, our intergalactic visitor from last year, made a surprise landing! She&#039;d been missing Millsberry as much as we&#039;ve been missing her.<br><br>&quot;Of all the places I could&#039;ve crash landed last year, I couldn&#039;t have stumbled upon a friendlier town. Every person I met was so cool&mdash;it was like finding a place where everyone was just like me!&quot;<br><br>She&#039;s delighted that people still wear the clothes inspired by her space fashion, and she swapped stories with a few citizens about their alien pets.<br>
<br>
&quot;One girl named Sharon said her alien pet loves hanging out in the backyard. Where I come from, pets are always kept indoors. The pets in Millsberry are so lucky!&quot;<br><br>But the question on everyone&#039;s mind was, &quot;What has Jenneira been up to since we last saw her?&quot; <br><br>Well, for one thing, she&#039;s got a new ship! <br><br>&quot;Millsberry&#039;s citizens helped me find the pieces of my last ship and I was able to repair it well enough to get myself home,&quot; Jenneira explained. &quot;But I knew if I was going to do any serious traveling in the future I would need a new craft. This one is the latest, coolest model and is amazing to drive!&quot;<br><br>So is this the last we&#039;ll see of Jenneira?<br><br>&quot;I don&#039;t know when I&#039;ll be able to visit again, because I&#039;ll be really busy when I get back home. I&#039;ve been accepted to a program that trains people to be teachers. I was able to contact Mr. Fort about a month ago to tell him the good news. I want to be a mentor to younger people...even though I&#039;m very young myself!&quot;<br><br>Mr. Fort added, &quot;I told Jenneira she ought to come by and visit before starting her teacher training. We thought up the puzzle idea together to help stir up a little excitement in town. Looks like it worked!&quot; <br><br>But how was Jenneira able to contact Mr. Fort from so far away?<br><br>&quot;I won&#039;t get into too much detail here, but I basically used a new super-advanced email system! I&#039;m not a pro at it yet, but hopefully I can send some messages to Millsberry in the future. I&#039;m so glad to be back here&mdash;I just wish I could stay longer than a week!&quot;<br><br>We&#039;re all very pleased to have such a special visitor in town. July has certainly been an eventful month!<br></div>


<br><hr><br>

<div id='gazette_story'>
<div align='center'><font size='3'><b>VISIT JENNEIRA!</b></font><br>
</div>
<br>
Wondering where you can see Jenneira? She&#039;s parked at her favorite spot&mdash;the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/crater/ship.phtml">clearing</a> behind the Westridge crater. Stop by this week and see if she&#039;s around, though she might be out and about with friends. If you&#039;ve been looking out for Mr. Fort this month, you just might get a cool prize at the clearing for collecting puzzle pieces. <br><br>Loretta Rivers is so thrilled that her fashion muse is back that she extended the sale on Jenneira-inspired clothing for another week! Why not head to the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing Store</a> and purchase a space outfit to wear to the Westridge clearing?</div>
